link_effecttoeffect10.setLinkType(LinkType.DIRECT);link_effecttoeffect10.getDescriptionIDs().set(new DescriptionSection(link_effecttoeffect10,dataSource,"Description","<div class='description'><h3>Description</h3><p><p>Impairment of testosterone production in testes directly impacts on testosterone levels.</p>\n\n</p></div><div class='references'><h3>References</h3><p><p>Akingbemi, B. T. 2001. &ldquo;Modulation of Rat Leydig Cell Steroidogenic Function by Di(2-Ethylhexyl)Phthalate.&rdquo; Biology of Reproduction 65 (4) (October 1): 1252&ndash;1259. doi:10.1095/biolreprod65.4.1252.</p>\n\n<p>Borch, Julie, Ole Ladefoged, Ulla Hass, and Anne Marie Vinggaard. 2004. &ldquo;Steroidogenesis in Fetal Male Rats Is Reduced by DEHP and DINP, but Endocrine Effects of DEHP Are Not Modulated by DEHA in Fetal, Prepubertal and Adult Male Rats.&rdquo; Reproductive Toxicology (Elmsford, N.Y.) 18 (1): 53&ndash;61. doi:10.1016/j.reprotox.2003.10.011.</p>\n\n<p>Borch, Julie, Stine Broeng Metzdorff, Anne Marie Vinggaard, Leon Brokken, and Majken Dalgaard. 2006. &ldquo;Mechanisms Underlying the Anti-Androgenic Effects of Diethylhexyl Phthalate in Fetal Rat Testis.&rdquo; Toxicology 223 (1-2) (June 1): 144&ndash;55. doi:10.1016/j.tox.2006.03.015.</p>\n\n<p>Culty, Martine, Raphael Thuillier, Wenping Li, Yan Wang, Daniel B Martinez-Arguelles, Carolina Gesteira Benjamin, Kostantinos M Triantafilou, Barry R Zirkin, and Vassilios Papadopoulos. 2008. &ldquo;In Utero Exposure to Di-(2-Ethylhexyl) Phthalate Exerts Both Short-Term and Long-Lasting Suppressive Effects on Testosterone Production in the Rat.&rdquo; Biology of Reproduction 78 (6) (June): 1018&ndash;28. doi:10.1095/biolreprod.107.065649.</p>\n\n<p>Hannas, Bethany R, Christy S Lambright, Johnathan Furr, Nicola Evans, Paul M D Foster, Earl L Gray, and Vickie S Wilson. 2012. &ldquo;Genomic Biomarkers of Phthalate-Induced Male Reproductive Developmental Toxicity: A Targeted RT-PCR Array Approach for Defining Relative Potency.&rdquo; Toxicological Sciences : An Official Journal of the Society of Toxicology 125 (2) (February): 544&ndash;57. doi:10.1093/toxsci/kfr315.</p>\n\n<p>Parks, L. G. 2000. &ldquo;The Plasticizer Diethylhexyl Phthalate Induces Malformations by Decreasing Fetal Testosterone Synthesis during Sexual Differentiation in the Male Rat.&rdquo; Toxicological Sciences 58 (2) (December 1): 339&ndash;349. doi:10.1093/toxsci/58.2.339.</p>\n\n<p>Shultz, V. D. 2001. &ldquo;Altered Gene Profiles in Fetal Rat Testes after in Utero Exposure to Di(n-Butyl) Phthalate.&rdquo; Toxicological Sciences 64 (2) (December 1): 233&ndash;242. doi:10.1093/toxsci/64.2.233.</p>\n\n<p>Wilson, Vickie S., Christy Lambright, Johnathan Furr, Joseph Ostby, Carmen Wood, Gary Held, and L.Earl Gray. 2004. &ldquo;Phthalate Ester-Induced Gubernacular Lesions Are Associated with Reduced insl3 Gene Expression in the Fetal Rat Testis.&rdquo; Toxicology Letters 146 (3) (February): 207&ndash;215. doi:10.1016/j.toxlet.2003.09.012.</p>\n\n</p></div>").setFormat(ContentFormat.HTML).<DescriptionSection> makeItLive(), 0);
