link_effecttoeffect13.setLinkType(LinkType.INDIRECT);link_effecttoeffect13.getDescriptionIDs().set(new DescriptionSection(link_effecttoeffect13,dataSource,"Description","<div class='description'><h3>Description</h3><p><p>Activation of PPAR&alpha; leads to decreased expression of cholesterol transport (TSPO) gene in steroidogenic cells (e.g. Leydig cell) and as a consequence the amount of cholesterol transported into mitochondria decreases (impact on steroid production).</p>\n\n</p></div><div class='references'><h3>References</h3><p><p>Bility, Moses T, Jerry T Thompson, Richard H McKee, Raymond M David, John H Butala, John P Vanden Heuvel, and Jeffrey M Peters. 2004. &ldquo;Activation of Mouse and Human Peroxisome Proliferator-Activated Receptors (PPARs) by Phthalate Monoesters.&rdquo; Toxicological Sciences : An Official Journal of the Society of Toxicology 82 (1) (November): 170&ndash;82. doi:10.1093/toxsci/kfh253.</p>\n\n<p>Boberg, Julie, Stine Metzdorff, Rasmus Wortziger, Marta Axelstad, Leon Brokken, Anne Marie Vinggaard, Majken Dalgaard, and Christine Nellemann. 2008. &ldquo;Impact of Diisobutyl Phthalate and Other PPAR Agonists on Steroidogenesis and Plasma Insulin and Leptin Levels in Fetal Rats.&rdquo; Toxicology 250 (2-3) (September 4): 75&ndash;81. doi:10.1016/j.tox.2008.05.020.</p>\n\n<p>Borch, Julie, Stine Broeng Metzdorff, Anne Marie Vinggaard, Leon Brokken, and Majken Dalgaard. 2006. &ldquo;Mechanisms Underlying the Anti-Androgenic Effects of Diethylhexyl Phthalate in Fetal Rat Testis.&rdquo; Toxicology 223 (1-2) (June 1): 144&ndash;55. doi:10.1016/j.tox.2006.03.015.</p>\n\n<p>Campioli, Enrico, Amani Batarseh, Jiehan Li, and Vassilios Papadopoulos. 2011. &ldquo;The Endocrine Disruptor Mono-(2-Ethylhexyl) Phthalate Affects the Differentiation of Human Liposarcoma Cells (SW 872).&rdquo; Edited by Vasu D. Appanna. PloS One 6 (12) (January 21): e28750. doi:10.1371/journal.pone.0028750.</p>\n\n<p>Gazouli, M. 2002. &ldquo;Effect of Peroxisome Proliferators on Leydig Cell Peripheral-Type Benzodiazepine Receptor Gene Expression, Hormone-Stimulated Cholesterol Transport, and Steroidogenesis: Role of the Peroxisome Proliferator-Activator Receptor .&rdquo; Endocrinology 143 (7) (July 1): 2571&ndash;2583. doi:10.1210/en.143.7.2571.</p>\n\n<p>Hannas, Bethany R, Christy S Lambright, Johnathan Furr, Nicola Evans, Paul M D Foster, Earl L Gray, and Vickie S Wilson. 2012. &ldquo;Genomic Biomarkers of Phthalate-Induced Male Reproductive Developmental Toxicity: A Targeted RT-PCR Array Approach for Defining Relative Potency.&rdquo; Toxicological Sciences : An Official Journal of the Society of Toxicology 125 (2) (February): 544&ndash;57. doi:10.1093/toxsci/kfr315.</p>\n\n<p>Hurst, Christopher H, and David J Waxman. 2003. &ldquo;Activation of PPARalpha and PPARgamma by Environmental Phthalate Monoesters.&rdquo; Toxicological Sciences : An Official Journal of the Society of Toxicology 74 (2) (August): 297&ndash;308. doi:10.1093/toxsci/kfg145.</p>\n\n<p>Lapinskas, Paula J., Sherri Brown, Lisa M. Leesnitzer, Steven Blanchard, Cyndi Swanson, Russell C. Cattley, and J. Christopher Corton. 2005. &ldquo;Role of PPAR&alpha; in Mediating the Effects of Phthalates and Metabolites in the Liver.&rdquo; Toxicology 207 (1): 149&ndash;163.</p>\n\n<p>Lehmann, Kim P, Suzanne Phillips, Madhabananda Sar, Paul M D Foster, and Kevin W Gaido. 2004. &ldquo;Dose-Dependent Alterations in Gene Expression and Testosterone Synthesis in the Fetal Testes of Male Rats Exposed to Di (n-Butyl) Phthalate.&rdquo; Toxicological Sciences : An Official Journal of the Society of Toxicology 81 (1) (September 1): 60&ndash;8. doi:10.1093/toxsci/kfh169.</p>\n\n<p>Pinelli, Alessandra, Cristina Godio, Antonio Laghezza, Nico Mitro, Giuseppe Fracchiolla, Vincenzo Tortorella, Antonio Lavecchia, et al. 2005. &ldquo;Synthesis, Biological Evaluation, and Molecular Modeling Investigation of New Chiral Fibrates with PPARalpha and PPARgamma Agonist Activity.&rdquo; Journal of Medicinal Chemistry 48 (17) (August 25): 5509&ndash;19. doi:10.1021/jm0502844.</p>\n\n<p>Schultz, R, W Yan, J Toppari, A V&ouml;lkl, J A Gustafsson, and M Pelto-Huikko. 1999. &ldquo;Expression of Peroxisome Proliferator-Activated Receptor Alpha Messenger Ribonucleic Acid and Protein in Human and Rat Testis.&rdquo; Endocrinology 140 (7) (July): 2968&ndash;75. doi:10.1210/endo.140.7.6858.</p>\n\n<p>Ward, J M, J M Peters, C M Perella, and F J Gonzalez. 1998. &ldquo;Receptor and Nonreceptor-Mediated Organ-Specific Toxicity of di(2-Ethylhexyl)phthalate (DEHP) in Peroxisome Proliferator-Activated Receptor Alpha-Null Mice.&rdquo; Toxicologic Pathology 26 (2): 240&ndash;6.</p>\n\n<p>Willson, T M, P J Brown, D D Sternbach, and B R Henke. 2000. &ldquo;The PPARs: From Orphan Receptors to Drug Discovery.&rdquo; Journal of Medicinal Chemistry 43 (4) (February 24): 527&ndash;50.</p>\n\n<p>Xie, Yi, Qian Yang, and Joseph W DePierre. 2002. &ldquo;The Effects of Peroxisome Proliferators on Global Lipid Homeostasis and the Possible Significance of These Effects to Other Responses to These Xenobiotics: An Hypothesis.&rdquo; Annals of the New York Academy of Sciences 973 (November): 17&ndash;25.</p>\n\n</p></div>").setFormat(ContentFormat.HTML).<DescriptionSection> makeItLive(), 0);
