link_effecttoeffect15.setLinkType(LinkType.DIRECT);link_effecttoeffect15.getDescriptionIDs().set(new DescriptionSection(link_effecttoeffect15,dataSource,"Description","<div class='description'><h3>Description</h3><p><p>Impairment in the normal development of the male reproductive tract (e.g. genital abnormality and/or cryptorchidism) can impact on fertility later in life.</p>\n\n</p></div><div class='references'><h3>References</h3><p><p>Asklund, C, T K Jensen, K M Main, T Sobotka, N E Skakkebaek, and N J&oslash;rgensen. 2010. &ldquo;Semen Quality, Reproductive Hormones and Fertility of Men Operated for Hypospadias.&rdquo; International Journal of Andrology 33 (1) (February): 80&ndash;7. doi:10.1111/j.1365-2605.2009.00957.x.</p>\n\n<p>Bracka, A. 1989. &ldquo;A Long-Term View of Hypospadias.&rdquo; British Journal of Plastic Surgery 42 (3) (May): 251&ndash;5.</p>\n\n<p>Cowin, Prue A, Elspeth Gold, Jasna Aleksova, Moira K O&rsquo;Bryan, Paul M D Foster, Hamish S Scott, and Gail P Risbridger. 2010. &ldquo;Vinclozolin Exposure in Utero Induces Postpubertal Prostatitis and Reduces Sperm Production via a Reversible Hormone-Regulated Mechanism.&rdquo; Endocrinology 151 (2) (February): 783&ndash;92. doi:10.1210/en.2009-0982.</p>\n\n<p>Eisenberg, Michael L, Michael H Hsieh, Rustin Chanc Walters, Ross Krasnow, and Larry I Lipshultz. 2011. &ldquo;The Relationship between Anogenital Distance, Fatherhood, and Fertility in Adult Men.&rdquo; PloS One 6 (5) (January): e18973. doi:10.1371/journal.pone.0018973.</p>\n\n<p>Macleod, D J, R M Sharpe, M Welsh, M Fisken, H M Scott, G R Hutchison, A J Drake, and S van den Driesche. 2010. &ldquo;Androgen Action in the Masculinization Programming Window and Development of Male Reproductive Organs.&rdquo; International Journal of Andrology 33 (2) (April): 279&ndash;87. doi:10.1111/j.1365-2605.2009.01005.x.</p>\n\n<p>Mendiola, Jaime, Richard W Stahlhut, Niels J&oslash;rgensen, Fan Liu, and Shanna H Swan. 2011. &ldquo;Shorter Anogenital Distance Predicts Poorer Semen Quality in Young Men in Rochester, New York.&rdquo; Environmental Health Perspectives 119 (7) (July): 958&ndash;63. doi:10.1289/ehp.1103421.</p>\n\n<p>NTP. 2005. &ldquo;Multigenerational Reproductive Assessment by Continuous Breeding When Diethylhexylphthalate (CAS 117-81-7).&rdquo;</p>\n\n<p>Skakkebaek, N E, E Rajpert-De Meyts, and K M Main. 2001. &ldquo;Testicular Dysgenesis Syndrome: An Increasingly Common Developmental Disorder with Environmental Aspects.&rdquo; Human Reproduction (Oxford, England) 16 (5) (May): 972&ndash;8.</p>\n\n<p>Thorup, Jorgen, Robert McLachlan, Dina Cortes, Tamara R. Nation, Adam Balic, Bridget R. Southwell, and John M. Hutson. 2010. &ldquo;What Is New in Cryptorchidism and Hypospadias - A Critical Review on the Testicular Dysgenesis Hypothesis.&rdquo; Journal of Pediatric Surgery. doi:10.1016/j.jpedsurg.2010.07.030.</p>\n\n</p></div>").setFormat(ContentFormat.HTML).<DescriptionSection> makeItLive(), 0);
